Package org.icesoft.testclient.client

Class Summary
AuctionMonitorUpdatesClient This AuctionMonitorUpdatesClient will launch the standard ping and recieve-updates Actors, except one of the actors will be the BiddingAuctionMonitorActor.
Client This Client class is the superclass for Client instances that setup normal test Actor associations that do work.
ClientDescriptor All the configuration items for a client
ListeningChatClient This login client is implemented in the following way: It builds on the ping+receive-updates-receive-updated-views model, but adds a loginActor to the front of the actor queue.
SpoofingClient The idea behind the spoofer client is to submit a request on behalf of someone else, therefore, no logging in is required, and the Actor will likely be modified in source to do what's actually required
StandalonePingReceiveUpdatesClient This StandalonePingReceiveUpdatesClient launches two threads.
SyncTestPostbackClient This single client will launch three threads to do it's work.
TalkingChatClient This login client is implemented in the following way: It builds on the ping+receive-updates-receive-updated-views model, but adds a loginActor to the front of the actor queue.
TestReceiveUpdatesOnlyClient Just a brief test class to see if the calls to the receieve updates methods are in fact blocking calls.
TimezoneMultiViewClient This client defines 2 actors.
TimezonePostbackClient Class for Clicking on a timezone application window.
